#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:3
msgid "Reproducible interpreted scripts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:5
msgid ""
"In this tutorial, you will learn how to use Nix to create and run "
"reproducible interpreted scripts, also known as [shebang] scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:7
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:9
msgid "A working {ref}`Nix installation <install-nix>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:10
msgid "Familiarity with [Bash]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:12
msgid "A trivial script with non-trivial dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:14
msgid ""
"Take the following script, which fetches the content XML of a URL, converts "
"it to JSON, and formats it for better readability:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:16
msgid ""
"#! /bin/bash\n"
"\n"
"curl https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/releases.atom | xml2json | jq .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:22
msgid ""
"It requires the programs `curl`, `xml2json`, and `jq`. It also requires the "
"`bash` interpreter. If any of these dependencies are not present on the "
"system running the script, it will fail partially or altogether."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:26
msgid ""
"With Nix, we can declare all dependencies explicitly, and produce a script "
"that will always run on any machine that supports Nix and the required "
"packages taken from Nixpkgs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:28
msgid "The script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:30
msgid ""
"A [shebang] determines which program to use for running an interpreted "
"script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:35
msgid "We will use the shebang line `#!/usr/bin/env nix-shell`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:37
msgid ""
"[`env`] is a program available on most modern Unix-like operating systems at "
"the file system path `/usr/bin/env`. It takes a command name as argument and "
"will run the first executable by that name it finds in the directories "
"listed in the environment variable `$PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:42
msgid ""
"We use [`nix-shell` as a shebang interpreter]. It takes the following "
"parameters relevant for our use case:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:45
msgid "`-i` tells which program to use for interpreting the rest of the file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:46
msgid "`--pure` excludes most environment variables when the script is run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:47
msgid ""
"`-p` lists packages that should be present in the interpreter's environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:48
msgid "`-I` explicitly sets [the search path] for packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:50
msgid ""
"More details on the options can be found in the [`nix-shell` reference "
"documentation](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/nix-shell."
"html#options)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:55
msgid "Create a file named `nixpkgs-releases.sh` with the following content:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:57
msgid ""
"#!/usr/bin/env nix-shell\n"
"#! nix-shell -i bash --pure\n"
"#! nix-shell -p bash cacert curl jq python3Packages.xmljson\n"
"#! nix-shell -I nixpkgs=https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"archive/2a601aafdc5605a5133a2ca506a34a3a73377247.tar.gz\n"
"\n"
"curl https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/releases.atom | xml2json | jq .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:66
msgid ""
"The first line is a standard shebang. The additional shebang lines are a Nix-"
"specific construct:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:69
msgid ""
"With the `-i` option, `bash` is specified as the interpreter for the rest of "
"the file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:71
msgid ""
"In this case, the `--pure` option is enabled to prevent the script from "
"implicitly using programs that may already exist on the system on which the "
"script is run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:73
msgid "The `-p` option lists the packages required for the script to run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:75
msgid ""
"The command `xml2json` is provided by the package `python3Packages.xmljson`, "
"while `bash`, `jq`, and `curl` are provided by packages of the same name. "
"`cacert` must be present for SSL authentication to work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:79
msgid ""
"Use [search.nixos.org](https://search.nixos.org/packages) to find packages "
"providing the program you need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:82
msgid ""
"The parameter of `-I` refers to a specific Git commit of the Nixpkgs "
"repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:84
msgid ""
"This ensures that the script will always run with the exact same package "
"versions, everywhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:86
msgid "Make the script executable:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:88
msgid "chmod +x nixpkgs-releases.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:92
msgid "Run the script:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:94
msgid "./nixpkgs-releases.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/reproducible-scripts.md:98
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr "下一步"

